🧠 PART 0 — Open Everything
Step 1:
Open MongoDB Compass
Step 2:
Click "Connect" (big green button)
Step 3:
Wait till it connects
Step 4:
Now click "Open MongoDB Shell" (or "MONGOSH")

👉 A black terminal-like screen opens
👉 This is where you type commands

🧠 PART 1 — Create Database & Collection
Step 5: Type this 👇 and press ENTER
use schoolDB

👉 This creates database schoolDB

Step 6: Type this 👇 and press ENTER
db.createCollection("students")

👉 Now collection students is ready

🧠 PART 2 — INSERT DATA
Step 7: Insert ONE student

Type 👇 and press ENTER

db.students.insertOne({
  name: "Aryan",
  marks: 85
})

👉 Done! One student added

Step 8: Insert MANY students

Type 👇 and press ENTER

db.students.insertMany([
  {name: "Rahul", marks: 70},
  {name: "Priya", marks: 90},
  {name: "Neel", marks: 60}
])

👉 Now multiple students added

🧠 PART 3 — READ DATA
Step 9: See ALL data

Type 👇 and press ENTER

db.students.find()

👉 You will see all students

🧠 PART 4 — UPDATE DATA
Step 10: Update ONE student

Type 👇 and press ENTER

db.students.updateOne(
  {name: "Aryan"},
  {$set: {marks: 95}}
)

👉 Aryan’s marks changed to 95

Step 11: Update MANY students

Type 👇 and press ENTER

db.students.updateMany(
  {},
  {$set: {status: "active"}}
)

👉 All students now have status = active

🧠 PART 5 — DELETE DATA
Step 12: Delete ONE student

Type 👇 and press ENTER

db.students.deleteOne({name: "Neel"})

👉 Neel is removed

Step 13: Delete ALL students

Type 👇 and press ENTER

db.students.deleteMany({})

👉 Everything is deleted
